page.title: 15HOUSING: DANE END AREA
page.content: In{DANE END}there is a large estate of council houses (old and new) and private houses which are not more than 20 years old. {AMBER:}My house is a council house and about 65 years old. It has 3 bedrooms, a bathroom, living and kitchen. Outside there is a shed and toilet. Seven people share our house. {SALLY:}My house in Sacombe is at least 50 years old. It goes with my Dad's work - he is a gamekeeper. It has three bedrooms, a living room, kitchen and bathroom. Until recently the toilet was at the bottom of the garden. Six people share our house. {JEANETTE:}I live in a bungalow in Dane End which belongs to my Mum and Dad. It is three years old. It has four bedrooms, a bathroom, living room and kitchen.There is a double garage. Four people live in my house.
